OL,3,CYoung drivers buying fake policies
OL,4,Closing #2,000 on average, says insurer
OL,6,FInsurance giant Aviva has said it is
OL,7,Fdetecting rising number of ghost
OL,8,Fbroking cases ` and is warning young
OL,9,Fdrivers they could lose around #2,000
OL,10,Ftypically by buying a fake motor
OL,11,Finsurance policy.
OL,13,FThe insurer said young drivers aged 17
OL,14,Fto 25 are the primary target of ghost
OL,15,Fbrokers.
OL,17,FIts data indicates that, on average,
OL,18,Fyoung drivers are losing #2,000 each
OL,19,Fwhen they buy fake car insurance
OL,20,Fpolicies from ghost brokers.
